Project structure:
- Modular Structure, modules that are closely related and refer to a specific
domain are grouped together. You will find global setting in the root directory
such as models.py, db.py etc...

New packages can be created containing the necessery code, eg. users directory will contain
users schema, authentication, routers etc...


SQLModel combines SQLAlchemy with Pydentic, data validation out of the box.
Reduces redundancy, less code. 
Synchronous support to handle multiple requests concurrently
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GONyd0CUrPc

# Alembic - Pyproject_async configuration
https://alembic.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/tutorial.html#using-pep-621


# SERPAPI
run serp_api.py
From root:
$ python -m backend.app.providers.serp_api

